# Pipeline intermediate artefacts (raw + per-country processed).
# The production GeoJSONs consumed by the web UI live in web/data/, but we
# only commit the pre-compressed .gz companions — the raw files get large
# (Nigeria is ~100 MB after the GRID3 merge) and would bloat git history
# on every rebuild. The deploy and the live atlas only need the .gz; the
# .htaccess rewrite serves it to gzip-capable clients, which is every
# modern browser. Re-run `python3 -m pipeline.build --country XXX` to
# regenerate the raw file locally if you need it.
data/raw/
data/processed/*/
!data/processed/.gitkeep
web/data/*.geojson
!web/data/*.geojson.gz

# Editor / tooling
node_modules/
.tmp/
.idea/
